excerpt: 88 acres of indoor/outdoor art- & nature-based exhibits, greenhouses & landscaped grounds.
detail_description: Franklin Park Conservatory and Botanical Gardens is a sprawling 88-acre destination featuring both indoor and outdoor art and nature exhibits, as well as lush greenhouses and beautifully landscaped grounds. The conservatory offers seasonal displays, short-term art exhibitions, and permanent indoor biomes showcasing over 400 plant species from around the globe. Notably, it houses the largest private botanical garden collection of glass works by renowned artist Dale Chihuly.
name: Franklin Park Conservatory and Botanical Gardens
address: 1777 E Broad St, Columbus, OH 43203, USA

excerpt: Varied permanent & traveling art collections plus an American cafe & a gift shop.
detail_description: The Columbus Museum of Art offers a diverse range of attractions, including permanent and traveling art collections, an American cafe, and a gift shop. The museum also features kid-friendly activities like the Open Studio and thought-provoking exhibits such as Queer/Modern showcasing works by early 20th-century LGBTQ+ artists. Located on The Ohio State University's campus, visitors can explore The Wex, a creative lab and contemporary art gallery hosting innovative exhibitions like Meditation Ocean.
name: Columbus Museum of Art
address: 480 E Broad St, Columbus, OH 43215, USA

excerpt: This large educational science center offers interactive exhibits, working labs & planetarium shows.
detail_description: Located in Columbus, Ohio, the Center of Science and Industry (COSI) is a top science museum offering interactive exhibits, working labs, planetarium shows, and a variety of hands-on science exhibits covering themes like Oceans, Gadgets, and Energy. The museum also features a Little Kidspace for younger children and a permanent American Museum of Natural History Dinosaur Gallery. Visitors can enjoy dining at the on-site cafe and restaurant or shop at the gift shop.
name: Center of Science and Industry (COSI)
address: 333 W Broad St, Columbus, OH 43215, USA

excerpt: Park showcasing land & sea life with a hands-on tide pool, reptile house, kangaroo walkabout & more.
detail_description: The Columbus Zoo and Aquarium is a sprawling park located about 20 miles north of downtown, showcasing a wide variety of land and sea life. With over 10,000 animals from more than 500 species across six themed areas, visitors can enjoy hands-on experiences like the tide pool and Jack Hanna's Animal Encounters Village. The zoo also offers additional attractions such as the Wilds conservation center, Zoombezi Bay water park for summer fun, and an 18-hole Safari Golf Course.
name: Columbus Zoo and Aquarium
address: 4850 W Powell Rd, Powell, OH 43065, USA

excerpt: Grand Greek revival building completed in 1861 featuring historical art & public guided tours.
detail_description: The Ohio Statehouse, completed in 1861, is a grand Greek revival building that serves as the state Capitol and seat of governance for the Ohio state government. The structure underwent multiple design changes and was supervised by five architects before its completion. Influenced by Greek architecture, it exudes grandeur and tradition. Visitors are drawn to its historical art, including The Grand Stair Hall and the Rotunda.
name: Ohio Statehouse
address: 1 Capitol Sq, Columbus, OH 43215, USA

excerpt: Covered farmers’ market selling flowers, produce & handicrafts, with global dining options.
detail_description: North Market Downtown is a covered farmers' market offering a wide array of products such as flowers, produce, and handicrafts. It's also a hub for global dining options with influences from various countries like Somalia, El Salvador, Mexico, Yemen, and Vietnam. The market features over 30 vendors including butchers, bakers, grocers, and restaurants. Visitors can enjoy farm-to-table fare and innovative dishes created by talented chefs.
name: North Market Downtown
address: 59 Spruce St, Columbus, OH 43215, USA

excerpt: The laid-back German Village is known for charming brick houses built by 19th-century immigrants along Beck, Mohawk, and Deshler streets. Shops selling books, traditional fudge, and handmade jewelry mingle with art galleries, German pubs, American bistros, and artisan coffee shops. In summer, the Actors’ Theatre Columbus stages outdoor Shakespeare and other plays in Schiller Park with its fountains and flower beds.
detail_description: German Village is a charming neighborhood in Columbus, known for its 19th-century brick houses built by German immigrants. The area features a mix of shops selling books, handmade jewelry, and traditional fudge, alongside art galleries, German pubs, American bistros, and artisan coffee shops. In the summer, Schiller Park hosts outdoor Shakespeare and other plays. This downtown-adjacent district offers brick-lined streets with boutiques and restaurants. The entire neighborhood is on the National Register of Historic Places.
name: German Village
address: Columbus, OH, USA

excerpt: Historic home of Ohio State Buckeyes football team & site of university commencement ceremonies.
detail_description: Ohio Stadium, affectionately referred to as "The Horseshoe," is a historic gem nestled in the heart of Columbus, Ohio. This iconic venue serves as the proud home of the Ohio State Buckeyes football team and has become synonymous with college football culture. Designed by Howard Dwight Smith, it stands out as one of the earliest concrete stadiums, showcasing its unique horseshoe shape that fans adore.
name: Ohio Stadium
address: 411 Woody Hayes Dr, Columbus, OH 43210, USA

excerpt: Exhibits cover the state's history plus Ohio Village, an interactive re-creation of an 1860s town.
detail_description: The Ohio History Center is a must-visit for history enthusiasts of all ages. It offers interactive exhibits covering the state's history, including Ohio Village, an immersive re-creation of an 1860s town. Visitors can marvel at a mastodon skeleton and explore a hands-on Lustron house exhibit from the 1950s. The museum also showcases United States' involvement in World War I and features diverse collections, including preserved Civil War flags.
name: Ohio History Center
address: 800 E 17th Ave, Columbus, OH 43211, USA

detail_description: Nestled in the heart of downtown Columbus, the Scioto Mile Promenade is a stunning urban retreat that spans over 175 acres of beautifully landscaped parkland. This vibrant area seamlessly connects the city to the picturesque Scioto River and features an array of attractions, including interactive fountains and scenic trails perfect for biking or walking. The Scioto Mile is also a hub for community events throughout the year, hosting popular festivals like Jazz & Rib Fest and Winterfest that celebrate local culture and bring people together.
name: Scioto Mile Promenade
address: 233 S Civic Center Dr, Columbus, OH 43215, USA

excerpt: Short North Arts District is a hip, culture-rich area centered on N. High Street. Contemporary galleries fill converted warehouses, and the Wexner Center for the Arts hosts boundary-pushing exhibitions. Shops selling records, streetwear, and vintage clothes are interspersed with student-packed coffeehouses, craft-beer bars, and casual eateries. Programming at Short North Stage spans musicals and cutting-edge drama.
detail_description: Short North Arts District, located in Columbus, is a vibrant and trendy area known for its rich cultural scene. The district features contemporary galleries housed in converted warehouses, as well as the boundary-pushing exhibitions at the Wexner Center for the Arts. Visitors can explore boutique shopping, art galleries, dining options, and rooftop bars along the iconic High Street. The neighborhood also hosts events like the Gallery Hop and Holiday Hop, offering a blend of art, performance, and culinary delights.
name: Short North Arts District
address: Columbus, OH, USA

excerpt: Futuristic entertainment center with interactive puzzles, immersive rooms & digitally augmented art.
detail_description: Otherworld is an innovative and futuristic entertainment center located on the eastern outskirts of Columbus. This immersive art installation offers visitors a one-of-a-kind experience with interactive puzzles, surreal large-scale scenes, and digitally augmented art. Spanning 32,000 square feet, it features over 40 mixed reality playgrounds created by more than 40 artists. The exhibit combines various art forms including animation, digital fabrication, sculpting, metalworking, and special effects to create a captivating and ever-changing environment.
name: Otherworld
address: 5819 Chantry Dr, Columbus, OH 43232, USA

excerpt: Quiet park featuring landscape plants artistically trimmed to recreate a famous Seurat painting.
detail_description: Topiary Park, situated in the Discovery District of Downtown Columbus, is a unique and tranquil attraction for botany enthusiasts. It stands out as the only public park in the world featuring landscape plants meticulously trimmed to recreate Georges Seurat's famous post-impressionist painting 'A Sunday Afternoon on the Island of La Grande Jatte.' The brainchild of sculptor James T.
name: Topiary Park
address: 480 E Town St, Columbus, OH 43215, USA

excerpt: Professional hockey arena that hosts big-name bands, orchestra performances & diverse events.
detail_description: Nationwide Arena is a versatile venue located in the lively Arena District of Columbus, Ohio. It boasts an impressive 685,000 square feet and a seating capacity of 20,000. The arena's elegant design features terrazzo floors, brick pillars, and marble details. It has hosted various events including big-name bands, orchestra performances, and NHL games since its opening in 2000. As the home of the Columbus Blue Jackets, it offers an immersive fan experience for hockey enthusiasts.
name: Nationwide Arena
address: 200 W Nationwide Blvd, Columbus, OH 43215, USA

detail_description: The National Veterans Memorial and Museum in Columbus, Ohio is a unique and modern structure that pays tribute to service members from all branches of the U.S. military across various conflicts and peacetime. Unlike traditional war museums, this institution focuses on the personal stories of ordinary soldiers, sailors, pilots, medics, and others through intimate exhibits featuring photos, personal artifacts like letters and rations, as well as video testimonials.
name: National Veterans Memorial and Museum
address: 300 W Broad St, Columbus, OH 43215, USA

excerpt: Clippers' baseball field, featuring bars, concession stands, a picnic area & kids' club incentives.
detail_description: Nestled in the vibrant Arena District of downtown Columbus, Huntington Park is a must-visit destination for baseball enthusiasts and families alike. As the proud home of the Columbus Clippers, this impressive stadium boasts modern facilities while preserving the nostalgic charm that makes baseball so special. With its spacious layout spanning three levels and accommodating over 10,000 fans, it creates an electric atmosphere perfect for enjoying America's favorite pastime.
name: Huntington Park
address: 330 Huntington Park Ln, Columbus, OH 43215, USA

excerpt: Park featuring ongoing seasonal events, cafes, a reading room, gardens & a carousel.
detail_description: John F. Wolfe Columbus Commons is a vibrant urban park in the heart of the city, offering a variety of activities and attractions for visitors. The park features seasonal events, cafes, a reading room, gardens, and a carousel. With over 250 events annually, there's always something happening at the Commons, from open-air yoga classes to concerts and community events. The 6-acre facility also includes dining options and beautifully landscaped flower beds and gardens.
name: John F. Wolfe Columbus Commons
address: 160 S High St, Columbus, OH 43215, USA

excerpt: Exhibits trace the history of cartoon art, from comic strips to graphic novels, on the OSU campus.
detail_description: Nestled within the vibrant campus of The Ohio State University, the Billy Ireland Cartoon Library & Museum stands as a treasure trove for cartoon enthusiasts and art lovers alike. This remarkable institution boasts the largest collection of comic strip art globally, featuring an astounding 300,000 original cartoons alongside 2.5 million clippings from comic strips and newspapers. Visitors can delight in iconic works like 'Family Circus' and 'Peanuts,' evoking nostalgia for those who cherished Sunday morning comics.
name: Billy Ireland Cartoon Library & Museum
address: 1813 N High St, Columbus, OH 43210, USA

excerpt: Modern venue at OSU featuring contemporary art exhibitions, film screenings & performances.
detail_description: The Wexner Center for the Arts, located at The Ohio State University, is a dynamic venue that showcases contemporary art through various mediums such as exhibitions, film screenings, and performances. Despite recent changes in leadership, the center continues to attract art enthusiasts with its avant-garde and experimental offerings. Visitors can expect to encounter diverse works ranging from photography by Cindy Sherman to unconventional installations by William Kentridge.
name: Wexner Center for the Arts
address: 1871 N High St, Columbus, OH 43210, USA

excerpt: 7,000-acre park with forests, rivers & creeks offering water sports, trails & nature programs.
detail_description: Battelle Darby Creek Metro Park, located in Galloway, Ohio, covers over 7,000 acres of diverse landscapes including wetlands, forests, and prairies. The park offers a wide range of outdoor activities such as hiking, biking, fishing, hunting, cross-country skiing, canoeing and kayaking. Visitors can also witness the reintroduced American Bison roaming freely in enclosed pastures.
name: Battelle Darby Creek Metro Park
address: 1775 Darby Creek Dr, Galloway, OH 43119, USA

detail_description: Located in the Schumacher Place neighborhood near German Village, the Wagner-Hagans Auto Museum is a hidden gem for automotive enthusiasts. The museum boasts a diverse collection of vintage cars from the 1920s and 1930s, including Packards Dual-Cowls and limousines. Visitors can also explore a unique assortment of license plates and memorabilia while learning about the history of these classic vehicles.
name: Wagner-Hagans Auto Museum
address: 476 E Kossuth St, Columbus, OH 43206, USA

excerpt: Celebrated theater with ornate, Spanish-Baroque architecture features a wide range of performances.
detail_description: Nestled just south of the Ohio Statehouse, the stunning Ohio Theatre is a true gem of Spanish-Baroque architecture that has captivated audiences since its grand opening in 1928. Originally designed as a movie palace and variety show venue, this majestic theater features an impressive 21-foot chandelier and intricate details that transport visitors to another era.
name: Ohio Theatre
address: 39 E State St, Columbus, OH 43215, USA

excerpt: A 13-acre landscaped recreation area specializing in roses, plus perennial & herb gardens.
detail_description: Nestled in Ohio, the Columbus Park of Roses is a breathtaking 13-acre public garden that invites visitors to immerse themselves in the beauty of nature. This enchanting space boasts an impressive collection of over 12,000 roses across more than 400 varieties, including both a Formal Rose Garden with around 8,000 rosebushes and a Heritage Rose Garden showcasing historical blooms from before 1867.
name: Columbus Park of Roses
address: 3901 N High St, Columbus, OH 43214, USA

excerpt: Historic home & garden, once a stop on the Underground Railroad, with exhibits on 19th-century life.
detail_description: The Kelton House Museum & Garden in Columbus, Ohio is a historic mansion with Greek revival and Italianate architecture. It was once a crucial stop on the Underground Railroad and played a significant role in 19th-century history. The serene house, surrounded by pastureland, was occupied by the Kelton family until 1975 when it was bequeathed to the Columbus Foundation.
name: Kelton House Museum & Garden
address: 586 E Town St, Columbus, OH 43215, USA

excerpt: Interactive museum in the home of writer James Thurber, with a literary center, tours & bookstore.
detail_description: Thurber House, located in the Jefferson Avenue Historic District, was once the residence of renowned American author and cartoonist James Thurber. This historic house is now an interactive museum featuring a literary center, offering self-guided tours of the National Register-listed property. Visitors can explore a sculpture garden and enjoy rotating art and literary events. The house also hosts writing workshops and special evenings with authors, making it a haven for literature enthusiasts.
name: Thurber House
address: 77 Jefferson Ave, Columbus, OH 43215, USA

detail_description: Located in Easton Town Center, Columbus, LEGOLAND Discovery Center is a vibrant and entertaining family attraction spanning 30,000 square feet. With six Lego-themed attractions including Miniland, a 4D cinema, interactive rides like Kingdom Quest and Merlins Apprentice, and a Lego Factory Tour, there's plenty to keep both kids and adults entertained for 2-3 hours. The center also features a preschooler program and hosts special events.
name: LEGOLAND Discovery Center Columbus
address: 157 Easton Town Ctr, Columbus, OH 43219, USA

detail_description: The Ohio Craft Museum, also known as the Ohio Designer Craftsmen, is a must-visit for art enthusiasts and creative individuals. This vibrant destination offers free entry to its rotating exhibitions featuring various art forms such as ceramics, glasswork, and fiber art. The museum also hosts workshops and programs for artists of all ages. Additionally, visitors can purchase craft supplies while exploring the diverse techniques showcased in the exhibits.
name: Ohio Craft Museum
address: 1665 W 5th Ave, Columbus, OH 43212, USA

detail_description: If you're in Columbus during the week, make sure to visit the Orton Geological Museum at The Ohio State University. This museum houses a 24-foot skeleton of Cryolophosauraus ellioti, along with various dinosaur bones and teeth, including those from a Mammoth and Mastodon. You can also see a full-size replica of a TRex skull, a giant sloth skeleton, fluorescent minerals, an Ohio-landed meteorite, crystals, and other fossils.
name: Orton Geological Museum
address: 155 S Oval Mall, Columbus, OH 43210, USA

excerpt: Nature preserve featuring formal gardens & lawns, a trail, with a center for workshops & a library.
detail_description: Inniswood Metro Gardens is a serene 122-acre nature preserve and botanical garden located just 15 minutes away from downtown Columbus. It offers a peaceful escape with formal gardens, lawns, and a variety of flora and fauna. The garden features over 2,000 plant species and friendly woodland wildlife. While it can get crowded on weekends, visiting on a quieter weekday allows for a more tranquil experience.
name: Inniswood Metro Gardens
address: 940 S Hempstead Rd, Westerville, OH 43081, USA

excerpt: Unique performance-arts venue & cafe staging rock musicals & sketch comedies in daytime & evening.
detail_description: Shadowbox Live is a renowned performance-arts venue and cafe in Columbus, known for staging rock musicals, sketch comedies, and original works year-round. Established in 1988 as an all-volunteer ensemble, this award-winning nonprofit troupe has found its home in the Brewery District since 2011. The venue includes a main stage, Backstage Bistro for visiting performers, and is operated by troupe members.
name: Shadowbox Live
address: 503 S Front St #260, Columbus, OH 43215, USA

excerpt: Chain retailers & specialty shops in a modern mall with kiddie events, play areas & a food court.
detail_description: Polaris Fashion Place is a modern mall featuring a mix of chain retailers and specialty shops, along with kiddie events, play areas, and a food court. During the summer months, visitors can enjoy free live music performances on Thursday nights. The mall boasts over 200 stores and restaurants including popular brands like Apple, Lululemon, H&M, and Macy's.
name: Polaris Fashion Place
address: 1500 Polaris Pkwy, Columbus, OH 43240, USA

excerpt: Bird habitats plus hiking, fishing, volleyball, dog parks & a climbing wall on 120 riverside acres.
detail_description: Discover the natural beauty and adventure at Scioto Audubon Metro Park, a 120-acre urban oasis in Columbus, Ohio. This wildlife preserve offers diverse habitats for local wildlife and features boardwalks through wetlands, perfect for observing migratory birds. The park also boasts a climbing wall, fishing opportunities, volleyball courts, and dog parks where your furry friends can roam off-leash.
name: Scioto Audubon Metro Park
address: 400 W Whittier St, Columbus, OH 43215, USA

detail_description: ZipZone Outdoor Adventures in Columbus, Ohio is a must-visit for thrill-seekers and families alike. The park offers a variety of outdoor activities, including canopy-top zip lines, ropes courses, and a kids park. With over 60 challenging elements spread across the parklands, visitors can enjoy an adrenaline-pumping experience. The guided multi-zipline tour takes you through the stunning Ohio treetops for an unforgettable adventure.
name: ZipZone Outdoor Adventures
address: 7925 N High St, Columbus, OH 43235, USA

excerpt: Series of circular fountains with interactive splash pads, nightly light shows & Scioto River views.
detail_description: The Scioto Mile Fountain is a captivating water feature located in Columbus, Ohio. It is the focal point of the Bicentennial Park and Scioto Mile, which offers 253 acres of picturesque parkland and various attractions. The fountain spans 15,000 square feet and boasts over 1,000 spraying jets that propel water up to 75 feet into the air.
name: Scioto Mile Fountain
address: Columbus, OH 43215, USA

excerpt: 1908 engine house, now a museum offering firefighting history exhibits & fire safety education.
detail_description: The Central Ohio Fire Museum is a captivating destination nestled in Downtown Columbus, housed within the historic Engine House No. 16, which dates back to 1908. This museum serves as a tribute to the rich history of firefighting in Ohio, showcasing an impressive array of exhibits that include hand-drawn and motorized fire apparatus. Visitors can immerse themselves in interactive displays that highlight the daily lives of firefighters while enjoying educational experiences about fire safety.
name: Central Ohio Fire Museum, llc
address: 260 N 4th St, Columbus, OH 43215, USA

detail_description: For golf enthusiasts and fans of the sport, a visit to the Jack Nicklaus Museum is an unforgettable experience. Nestled within The Ohio State University Sports Complex, this museum celebrates the illustrious career of Columbus native Jack Nicklaus, who is revered as one of golf's greatest players. The museum showcases an extensive collection of memorabilia that chronicles his journey from a young golfer to a legendary figure with 18 major championships under his belt.
name: Jack Nicklaus Museum
address: 2355 Olentangy River Rd, Columbus, OH 43210, USA

detail_description: Nestled in the vibrant King-Lincoln District of Columbus, The King Arts Complex stands as a beacon of African American heritage and culture. Since its inception in 1987, this dynamic institution has become a hub for community engagement through various exhibits, educational programs, and performance arts that celebrate the significant contributions of influential African Americans throughout history.
name: The King Arts Complex
address: 835 Mt Vernon Ave, Columbus, OH 43203, USA

excerpt: Native American burial grounds, 100-ft.-high bluffs with river views & 11 miles of hiking trails.
detail_description: Highbanks Metro Park is a popular destination within the Metro Parks System, offering stunning natural features and diverse hiking trails. The park is named for its impressive 100-foot tall sandstone bluffs that provide breathtaking views of the Olentangy State Scenic River. Visitors can explore 11 miles of trails, including the challenging Coyote Run and Overlook trails, which wind through forests, meadows, and shale ravines.
name: Highbanks Metro Park
address: 9466 Columbus Pike, Lewis Center, OH 43035, USA

excerpt: Urban public space with 15,000-sq.-ft. Scioto Mile Fountain, outdoor stage & glass-enclosed eatery.
detail_description: Bicentennial Park, also known as John W. Galbreath Bicentennial Park, is a 4.66-acre urban public space located in downtown Columbus. The park features the impressive Scioto Mile Fountain, a 15,000-square-foot masterpiece with over 1,000 water jets and unique lighting and fog effects that make it interactive and accessible to all ages.
name: Bicentennial Park
address: 233 S Civic Center Dr, Columbus, OH 43215, USA

excerpt: Longtime green space featuring a fishing pond, playground & tennis courts, plus a stage for shows.
detail_description: Schiller Park, located in the charming German Village neighborhood just south of downtown Columbus, is a historic green space with a rich cultural heritage. Originally established in the mid-1800s and later renamed after the renowned German poet Friedrich Schiller, the park offers various attractions such as a fishing pond, playground, tennis courts, and a stage for outdoor shows. The area also features traces of German-American culture, including spots like Schmidts sausage haus and a bronze statue of Friedrich Schiller.
name: Schiller Park
address: 1069 Jaeger St, Columbus, OH 43206, USA

excerpt: City park with skyline views surrounded by Victorian homes & featuring a playground & tennis.
detail_description: Goodale Park, established in 1851, is the oldest public park in Columbus and one of the oldest in the country. Surrounded by Victorian homes, this historic park offers picturesque skyline views and a serene atmosphere. Visitors can enjoy various amenities such as tennis courts, a playground, picnic areas, and a gazebo. The lush greenery and a charming duck-filled pond with a fountain make it an ideal spot for leisurely strolls or family outings.
name: Goodale Park
address: 120 W Goodale St, Columbus, OH 43215, USA

excerpt: Water park with a giant pool & raft slides, high-speed mat races, a lazy river & more.
detail_description: Zoombezi Bay is a thrilling water park located next to the Columbus Zoo and Aquarium, offering a perfect blend of refreshing water attractions and spooky, zombie-themed experiences. The park features a giant pool, raft slides, high-speed mat races, lazy rivers, and more. In addition to its water rides, Zoombezi Bay also boasts haunted houses and scare zones for horror enthusiasts. Visitors can enjoy non-water rides like the Sea Dragon roller coaster as well.
name: Zoombezi Bay
address: 4850 Powell Rd, Powell, OH 43065, USA

detail_description: American Whistle Corporation, located in Columbus, Ohio, is the sole manufacturer of metal whistles in the United States. Established in 1956, this company takes pride in producing high-quality solid brass whistles designed to last a lifetime. Visitors can enjoy a free guided tour of the factory to learn about the whistle-making process and even leave with their very own shiny new whistle as a souvenir. The tour provides insight into the materials used and how each component comes together to create these essential safety devices.
name: American Whistle Corp
address: 6540 Huntley Rd # B, Columbus, OH 43229, USA

detail_description: Nestled in the charming German Village, The Book Loft is a renowned independent bookstore that occupies a historic Pre-Civil War building. Boasting an impressive 32 rooms filled with over 750,000 books, it offers an extensive selection for all literary tastes. Beyond books, visitors can also find an array of gifts and t-shirts to peruse. This picturesque setting provides ample opportunities for bookish photo ops and leisurely browsing through its vast collection.
name: The Book Loft of German Village
address: 631 S 3rd St, Columbus, OH 43206, USA

detail_description: The Ohio Expo Center & State Fairgrounds in Columbus is a bustling cultural hub, hosting around 185 events annually. This expansive complex features over 20 exhibition buildings, an outdoor amphitheater, and a fairground that hosts prestigious events like the All-American Quarter Horse Congress and Equine Affaire. The center has been the permanent home of the Ohio State Fair since 1886 and continues to expand, now offering over 1 million square feet of event space.
name: Ohio Expo Center & State Fair
address: 717 E 17th Ave, Columbus, OH 43211, USA

excerpt: Live musical performances & other entertainment in a restored 19th-century theater.
detail_description: The Southern Theatre, dating back to the late 1800s, is a restored 19th-century theater and one of the oldest surviving theaters in central Ohio. It was one of the first landmarks in Columbus to use electricity. The venue hosts live musical performances, independent films, Broadway-style shows, and offers backstage tours throughout the year. Operated by the Columbus Association for the Performing Arts (CAPA), it continues to bring captivating entertainment experiences to its audience.
name: Southern Theatre
address: 21 E Main St, Columbus, OH 43215, USA

excerpt: Home of the Ohio State Buckeyes & host of an array of men's & women's sports events & concerts.
detail_description: The Schottenstein Center, also known as the Value City Arena at The Jerome Schottenstein Center, is a prominent venue located on the Ohio State University campus. It serves as the home for various men's and women's sports events and concerts. Hosting over 200 events annually, including concerts featuring renowned artists like Lady Gaga and Justin Timberlake, it has become an iconic arena with a rich history of entertainment.
name: The Schottenstein Center
address: 555 Borror Dr, Columbus, OH 43210, USA

excerpt: Park featuring a 35-ft. waterfall & an overlook accessed via a boardwalk, plus picnic tables.
detail_description: Hayden Falls Park is a serene natural spot located near a bustling shopping center in Columbus, OH. The park features a 35-ft. waterfall formed by the River Scioto curving a gorge close to the Griggs Reservoir. Visitors can access an overlook via a boardwalk and enjoy picnic tables amidst lush surroundings.
name: Hayden Falls Park
address: 4326 Hayden Run Rd, Dublin, OH 43017, USA

excerpt: In the hip Brewery District, craft beer bars and music venues occupy converted Victorian breweries. The area’s lively dining scene encompasses gastropubs, tapas spots, and farm-to-table restaurants. Shadowbox Live stages experimental theater, comedy, and dance. Developed on industrial wasteland, Scioto Audubon Metro Park is a riverside green space with trails, a climbing wall, and birdlife such as peregrine falcons.
detail_description: The Brewery District in Columbus, Ohio is a vibrant area filled with craft beer bars, music venues, and converted Victorian breweries. The dining scene offers a variety of options including gastropubs, tapas spots, and farm-to-table restaurants. Visitors can also enjoy experimental theater, comedy, and dance at Shadowbox Live. The Scioto Audubon Metro Park provides a riverside green space with trails, a climbing wall, and diverse birdlife.
name: Brewery District
address: Columbus, OH, USA

excerpt: Museum displaying a large collection of rare, vintage  television sets & studio equipment.
detail_description: This small museum is stuffed full of old televisions and other studio equipment used to create television shows. If you're a fan of watching your favorite shows, this is the place for you!
name: Early Television Museum
address: 5396 Franklin St, Hilliard, OH 43026, USA
